<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"NCAA_formula">NCAA formula<=
/h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPasser_ratin=
g&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: NCAA formula"><=
span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span><=
/div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Collegiate_Athleti=
c_Association" title=3D"National Collegiate Athletic Association">NCAA</a> =
passing efficiency formula is similar to that of the NFL passer rating, but=
 does not impose limits on the four components. The formula is based on col=
lege football data between 1965 and 1978, and when the formula was first cr=
eated, a 100 passer efficiency indicated an average performance.
</p><p>The passing efficiency formula is:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Passer_rating#cite_note-6=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup>
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><=
math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle=
 {\text{Passer Efficiency}}_{\text{NCAA}}=3D{(8.4\times {\text{YDS}})+(330\=
times {\text{TDP}})+(100\times {\text{CMP}})-(200\times {\text{INT}}) \over=
 {\text{ATT}}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mtext>Passer Efficiency</mtext>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mtext>NCAA</mtext>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>8.4</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>YDS</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>330</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>TDP</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>100</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>CMP</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>200</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mtext>INT</mtext>
              </mrow>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mtext>ATT</mtext>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\text{Passer=
 Efficiency}}_{\text{NCAA}}=3D{(8.4\times {\text{YDS}})+(330\times {\text{T=
DP}})+(100\times {\text{CMP}})-(200\times {\text{INT}}) \over {\text{ATT}}}=
}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/dd0a529fc91d359f620c5cccbfaa9d03d563988f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.005ex; width:86.125ex; height:5.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
text{Passer Efficiency}}_{\text{NCAA}}=3D{(8.4\times {\text{YDS}})+(330\tim=
es {\text{TDP}})+(100\times {\text{CMP}})-(200\times {\text{INT}}) \over {\=
text{ATT}}}}"></span>
</p><p>where
</p>
<dl><dd><b>ATT</b> =3D Number of passing attempts</dd>
<dd><b>CMP</b> =3D Number of completions</dd>
<dd><b>YDS</b> =3D Passing yards</dd>
<dd><b>TDP</b> =3D Touchdown passes</dd>
<dd><b>INT</b> =3D Interceptions</dd></dl>
<p>The NCAA passer efficiency has an upper limit of 1,261.6 (every attempt =
is a 99-yard completion for a touchdown), and a lower limit of =E2=88=92731=
.6 (every attempt is completed, but results in a 99-yard loss).  A passer w=
ho throws only interceptions will have a =E2=88=92200 efficiency, as would =
a passer who only throws completed passes losing an average of 35.714 yards=
.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Advantages">Advantages</h2>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPasser_rating&am=
p;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Advantages"><span>e=
dit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In 2011, <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sports_Illustrated"=
 title=3D"Sports Illustrated">Sports Illustrated</a></i> published an artic=
le by Kerry Byrne of <i>Cold Hard Football Facts</i> highlighting the impor=
tance of passer rating in determining a team's success.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Passer_rati=
ng#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">]</span></a></sup> "Put most simply," the article states, "you cann=
ot be a smart football analyst and dismiss passer rating. In fact, it's imp=
ossible to look at the incredible correlation of victory to passer rating a=
nd then dismiss it. You might as well dismiss the score of a game when dete=
rmining a winner. [...] Few, if any, are more indicative of wins and losses=
 than passer rating. Teams that posted a higher passer rating went 203=E2=
=80=9353 (.793) in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_NFL_season=
" title=3D"2010 NFL season">2010</a> and an incredible 151=E2=80=9329 (.839=
) after Week 5." Byrne made an expanded defense of the passer rating and it=
s importance for the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pro_Football_=
Researchers_Association" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Pro Football Resear=
chers Association">Pro Football Researchers Association</a> in 2012.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Passer_rating#cite_note-8"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>8<span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The study showed that all of the ei=
ght teams since 1940 that led the league in both offensive passer rating an=
d defensive passer rating won championships.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-9" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Passer_rating#cite_not=
e-9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</=
span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Flaws">Flaws</h2><span clas=
s=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DPasser_rating&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Flaws"><span>edit</span></a=
><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The passer rating equation does not take into account sacks, fumbles, or=
 a quarterback's rushing production, although by definition it only measure=
s passing statistics.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_10-0" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Passer_rating#cite_note-:0-10"><span cl=
ass=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></s=
up>=20
</p><p>Due to rule changes and improvement in quarterback play, the league-=
wide passer rating has increased by an average of 0.63 points per season si=
nce its introduction in 1973, from 61.7 that year to 93.6 in 2020, which ma=
kes passer rating a poor statistic for comparing quarterbacks from differen=
t seasons or eras.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Passer_rating#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Other_measurements">Other m=
